    INSTALLATION

Installation is possible on Unix-like systems with a C compiler: to install,
run `make' then `make install'; to uninstall, run `make uninstall'.

It should be necessary to run `make install' as root (DESTDIR is supported).

The following files and folders are installed to the following default
locations:

jsession -> /usr/bin/jsession
jsessiond -> /usr/bin/jsessiond
jsession-quit -> /usr/bin/jsession-quit
dbus.conf -> /etc/dbus-1/system.d/jsession.conf
conf -> /etc/jsession/conf
bash_completion -> /etc/bash_completion.d/jsession_quit

    DEPENDENCIES

Bash: http://www.gnu.org/software/bash
GNU grep or equivalent
DBus: http://www.freedesktop.org/wiki/Software/dbus
System V init (or compatible): http://savannah.nongnu.org/projects/sysvinit

    For suspend support (not required if using systemd):

pm-utils: http://pm-utils.freedesktop.org/wiki/

    To be able to run executables as root on login:

run-parts (part of debianutils):
    http://packages.qa.debian.org/d/debianutils.html

    USAGE

See `jsession --help' and `jsession-quit --help' for details.  Start the daemon
(as root) using `jsessiond', or write an init script (find a systemd service
file at the project homepage).
